  "original_title": "\u0d86\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9\u0dd4\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca \u0db4\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0d91\u0da2\u0dcf\u0db4 \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dc4\u0ddc\u0da7\u0dca\u0da7\u0dd4 \u0dc3\u0dd3\u0dad\u0dbd \u0dba\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dca\u0db0\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "UNP budding cold war to appoint governors",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Political sources say that there are signs that the appointment of governors for the nine provinces of the island will become a big mess.",
        "According to the sources, President Ranil Wickremesinghe has already decided to appoint several people related to the United National Party as governors and the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna has proposed separate names for the governorships.",
        "From the members of the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna in the appointment of the Governor for the Eastern Province",
        "It is reported that several MPs of the province, including former minister Mr. Wimalaweera Dissanayake, have already informed the government not to act illegally.",
        "The number of members of the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna representing the Eastern Province is 8.",
        "Former Minister Daya Gamage, John Amaratunga Naveen Dissanayake and former opposition leader Shamel Senarath of the North West Province have also proposed for the post of Governor.",
        "In the meantime, it has been learned that the party has requested the President to give three governors appointed by the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna government the opportunity to continue in those governorships.",
        "The persons who Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna has requested to be given the opportunity to continue working in the positions of governors are Lalith U Gamage, Willy Gamage and M. Messrs. J. Moosammil."
      ],
